        "created_at": "2025-11-22T20:38:29.876Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have Signal setup in Waydroid (Debian 13) but I cannot get the camera screen to show anything except a fully black screen.  However, when I open the camera app in Waydroid, it is able to use my USB webcam without issue.</p>\n<p>I don’t actually care about using the camera for video/pictures - I just want to link a device.  But when I go to “Linked devices” from Settings and then tap “Link a new device” I just get a black background (where I presume the camera’s output should go) and Signal tells me to “Scan the QR code”, which of course I can’t see.  So if there’s another method to do that, I’m happy to use it (though other threads I’ve seen here so far suggest without a camera there is no way).</p>\n<p>Does Signal use some non-default way of accessing the camera?  How do I get it to see the same camera that the camera app sees?  Note that I have already confirmed that the camera/mic permissions available to both Signal and the camera app are identical.</p>",
